# Personal site (wock9000.github.io)

This repository is a **personal** static site. Treat it as separate from employer or client codebases (e.g. Arteria / sync-ai): different repo path, different concerns, no shared session files like `CONTEXT.md` in this project.

## Recommended workflow (Cursor)

Open **`lighthouse.code-workspace`** in a **dedicated Cursor window** for all site work (or **File → Open Folder** and choose this repo, `wock9000.github.io`). This rule has **`alwaysApply: true`** here only: the agent picks it up automatically in that window—no paste-in context. Avoid mixing site edits into the primary Arteria workspace unless you use **`site-and-sync-ai.code-workspace`** on purpose.

### MCP and workspace root

**Cursor MCP tools use whatever workspace is open as the mount point.** If your root folder is another project (e.g. sync-ai / research), file operations and MCP-backed writes can land there instead of this site repo—forcing a detour or manual copy.

**To fix that permanently for site work:** before starting a session where you want agents or MCP to edit **`wock9000.github.io`**, open **this repository** as the workspace—**File → Open Folder** → select the site repo (or open **`lighthouse.code-workspace`** from it). Keep a separate Cursor window for other codebases when you need both.

## Stack

- Plain **HTML** and **CSS**; one shared `style.css`.
- **Root (`index.html`):** musings archive (list). No separate landing page.
- **Pieces** under `musings/`: plain HTML; deferred scripts allowed from the template: **`../assets/day-bg.js`**, **`../assets/epoch.js`**, **`../assets/epoch-delim-picker.js`** (footer clocks + Shift+click delimiter on desktop)—do not add other scripts. Piece headers use **`&lt;p class="date"&gt;YYYY-MM&lt;/p&gt;`** only (no human/unix hover swap). The **archive** (`index.html`) uses **`.entry-date.date-swap`** for optional unix-on-hover. New pieces: copy `musings/_template.html`, add a `<li>` to **`index.html`** at repo root (newest first).

## Do not add

- `CONTEXT.md` or other workspace session files meant for a different repo (also listed in **`.gitignore`** so they never ship by accident).
- Frameworks, Tailwind, React, npm build pipelines, or Jekyll unless the site owner asks for a migration.
- Secrets or credentials in any file.

## Assets

- GIFs or images: place under repo root or `assets/`; reference by relative path. Optional `.gif-block` slots exist in `musings/_template.html` (remove `hidden` to show).

## Cursor / VS Code workspaces

- **Site only (Lighthouse):** open **`lighthouse.code-workspace`** (or the repo folder). Keeps rules and tasks scoped to this repo.
- **Site + Arteria in one window:** open **`site-and-sync-ai.code-workspace`** when you need both trees; personal-site rules still apply only inside the site folder unless you add sync-ai rules separately.

## Local preview

- Run **`./scripts/serve.sh`** (or the **Serve site (local)** task in Cursor/VS Code) so the site is served over HTTP; refresh after edits.

## Git

- Default branch here is **`trunk`**. Match GitHub Pages settings to that branch (or document if you rename to `main`).
